{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a reformed income tax band system with gradual increases from 20-45%",
        "additional_details": "We think the current tax bands unfairly burden middle-income earners with sudden jumps, and that a gradual tax increase from 20% to 45% would prevent financial strain while ensuring fairness. We think this could generate an extra \u00a325\u201332 billion annually, which could be used for strengthening the NHS, education, and infrastructure. In our view, taxing higher incomes progressively while protecting low earners, creates a sustainable, balanced economy that rewards work and funds national priorities.",
        "background": "Introduce an income tax system where the 20% starting rate rises 1% every \u00a35k up to 40% then every \u00a310k up to 45%. Set the tax free personal allowance at the amount someone would earn from 39hrs work a week at minimum wage. We think it will help a smooth transition and boost funds to vital services.",
